description: TEHRAN- One day after Operation al-Aqsa Storm on October 7, Lebanon’s Hezbollah entered the battle in solidarity with Gaza.
title: Hezbollah’s unbreakable solidarity with Gaza

description: ISLAMABAD- Iran and Pakistan are neighboring countries, brothers, and friends. They share a common history and civilization that spans several hundred thousand years, creating an unbreakable bond between the two nations and governments in a way that the luminaries of both lands, such as Iqbal and Jinnah, Hafez and Saadi, and hundreds of other renowned figures, are equally respected by both nations.
title: Iran and Pakistan in the shadow of civilization and shared identity

description: TEHRAN - Pro-Palestine protests have snowballed across elite universities in the United States amid a violent police crackdown on students who call for ending Israel’s genocidal war in Gaza.
title: Campus crackdown abetting genocide

description: Ireland’s Minister of Foreign Affairs and Defense Micheal Martin has reiterated his country’s position on the recognition of a Palestinian state but said there were significant challenges in place.
title: Ireland ‘open to recognizing a Palestinian state’

description: In Nasser Hospital, southern Gaza’s main health facility, authorities are reported to have recovered a further 35 bodies from what they say is one of at least three mass graves found at the site, taking the total found there to 310 in the past week.
title: More bodies found in Khan Younis mass graves

description: Finland says it supports the activities of the UN relief works agency for Palestinians (UNRWA) across the region, with 10% of the country’s support for the agency this year earmarked for “risk management”.
title: Finland backs UNRWA activities

description: Britain’s plans to send some asylum-seekers to Rwanda were swiftly condemned by international humanitarian organizations after Parliament approved legislation allowing the deportation flights to begin later this year.
title: Human rights groups condemn UK Rwanda plan

description: India’s main opposition party accused Prime Minister Narendra Modi of using hate speech after he called Muslims “infiltrators” — some of his most incendiary rhetoric about the minority faith, days after the country began its weekslong general election.
title: Modi accused of using hate speech against Muslims

description: Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev has said that a peace deal with Armenia was closer than ever before, as teams from the two countries headed to the border to start demarcation work, hoping to end decades of territorial disputes.
title: Aliyev: Peace deal with Armenia 'closer than ever'

description: Russia will intensify strikes on Ukrainian storage bases that house Western-supplied weapons, Defense Minister Sergei Shoigu said on Tuesday, as the United States prepares to approve and deliver a long-delayed batch of new military aid, Reuters reported.
title: Russia to step up strikes on Western weapons in Ukraine

description: TEHRAN - There are renewed calls among Western media and Israeli-affiliated think tanks to up pressure on Iran after the country carried out a historic attack against the occupied territories with impressive success.
title: No more options against Iran

description: TEHRAN- Iraj Elahi, the ambassador of Iran to India, has said that Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi will pay a visit to India later this year.
title: President Raisi to visit India soon

description: TEHRAN - In an analysis, Javan dealt with the loss of Israel's defense reputation and said: What caused the loss of the reputation of the Iron Dome had several reasons, one of which was the help of the countries supporting this regime on the night of the operation.
title: The reputation of the defensive shield was lost

description: TEHRAN -The Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) has urged increased cooperation of Iran with the agency, despite the country’s full commitment to the issue.
title: IAEA chief urges Iran's cooperation amid alleged concerns

description: TEHRAN - Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi highlighted the potential for the Islamic Republic and Pakistan to significantly contribute to regional peace by strengthening their bilateral ties.
title: Iran, Pakistan vow to strengthen bilateral relations for regional peace

description: The Palestinian resistance movement Hamas has once again praised Iran’s missile and drone attack against Israel that was carried out earlier this month.
title: Hamas: Iran’s attack on Israel set new rules

description: Prominent literary group PEN America has canceled its annual award ceremony after dozens of nominated writers withdrew in protest of the Israeli war in Gaza, according to the BBC.
title: PEN America awards called off after writers' Gaza boycott

description: TEHRAN-An adaptation of English playwright and poet William Shakespeare’s play “Titus Andronicus” is currently on stage at Iranshahr Theater in Tehran.
title: Adaptation of “Titus Andronicus” on stage in Tehran

description: Columbia University officials have ordered classes to be held virtually as they seek to de-escalate tensions on the New York City campus during pro-Palestinian demonstrations.
title: Columbia University moves classes online after Gaza protests

description: TEHRAN-A Persian translation of the book “Polar Explorations” written by Don Nardo has been released in the book market across Iran.
title: “Polar Explorations” for young readers published in Persian

description: TEHRAN- Hossein Amir Abdollahian, the Foreign Minister of Iran, chastised the European Union for imposing harsher sanctions on the nation in retaliation for the latest round of massive drone and missile attacks on Israel, stating that the EU should not budge to Washington’s demands in order to placate the phony regime in Tel Aviv.
title: Amir Abdollahian slams EU over plans to impose new sanctions on Iran

description: TEHRAN- Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi congratulated the Syrian Arab Republic on its national day in a message to his Syrian counterpart on Monday.
title: Raisi felicitates Syria on National Day

description: TEHRAN - General Mohammad Bagheri, the chief of Iran’s Armed Forces Joint Staff, has emphasized the significant strategic shifts witnessed globally following Iran’s retaliation against the Zionist regime.
title: Military chief asserts Op. True Promise's ‘strategic impact globally’

description: TEHRAN-Iran and Pakistan will produce a film about Allama Muhammad Iqbal, known as Iqbal Lahori, the Minister of Culture and Islamic Guidance said after meetings with Pakistani officials in his trip to the neighboring country on Monday.
title: Iran, Pakistan to produce film about Iqbal Lahori

description: TEHRAN- The calligraphy section of the 21st edition of Imam Reza (AS) International Festival will host a number of master calligraphers from the Muslim world, the organizers have announced.
title: Imam Reza calligraphy festival welcoming artists from Muslim world

description: TEHRAN-In a meeting with the Chief Minister of Punjab Maryam Nawaz on Tuesday, Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi expressed Iran’s readiness to expand Persian language education in Pakistan.
title: Culture Minister tasked with expansion of Persian language education in Pakistan

description: TEHRAN - Tabriz, a city celebrated for its rich cooking heritage, is set to spotlight ‘culinary tourism’ as a major theme in this year's array of tourism events.
title: Tabriz puts culinary delights front and center in tourism agenda

description: TEHRAN – Situated in the north of Iran, Gilan province welcomed more than a thousand foreign tourists since the beginning of the Persian New Year [March 20] to secure its place as a sought-after destination across Iran.
title: Gilan flourishes with 30% surge in inbound tourism

description: TEHRAN – Showcasing the lesser-known relics coming from Iran’s National Museum, ten provincial exhibitions are in progress to take place within the Cultural Heritage Week before this Persian month is out.
title: Lesser-known relics to be staged in provincial exhibitions

description: TEHRAN - Several players of Iran national team have announced their withdrawal from the national team, with less than two months remaining to start of the 2024 Volleyball Nations League.
title: Mass resignation in Iran national volleyball team

description: TEHRAN – The second edition of a tribal festival dedicated to Shahsevan nomads will be held in Ardabil province on April 25 and 26.
title: Ardabil to host 2nd festival dedicated to Shahsevan nomads

description: Accompanied by a group of journalists, we recently embarked on a journey to explore the Zayandeh-Rud river, tracing its origins near Zard-Kuh, a sub-range in the central Zagros range in Chaharmahal-Bakhtiari province, all the way to the ancient city of Isfahan.
title: Dry river, sinking city: urgent measures needed to save Isfahan’s heritage

description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), dropped 13,420 points to 2,303,382 on Monday, which is the third day of the Iranian calendar week.
title: TEDPIX falls 13,000 points on Monday

description: TEHRAN – The Central Bank of Iran (CBI) provided $4.3 billion of foreign currency to the importers of medicine and medical equipment in the previous Iranian calendar year (ended on March 19).
title: CBI provides $4.3 billion to import medicine, medical equipment in a year

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s gold reserves saw unprecedented growth last year, especially over the past three months, Al Mayadeen reported citing reliable foreign sources.
title: Iran’s gold reserves rise unprecedentedly: report

description: TEHRAN – The loading and unloading of goods in the ports of Iran increased by four percent in the previous Iranian calendar year 1402 (ended on March 19), as compared to the same period in a year earlier, the data released by the country’s Transport and Urban Development Ministry showed.
title: Annual loading, unloading of goods in ports up 4%

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Oil Ministry and Atomic Energy Organization of Iran (AEOI) signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU) on Monday, April 22, to boost cooperation in a range of areas including technology.
title: Oil Ministry inks co-op MOU with AEOI

description: TEHRAN - The China Customs has announced that the trade exchanges between Iran and China stood at more than $4.0 billion from January to March 2024.
title: Iran-China trade exchange at $4b in Q1 2024

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji says Islamabad is eager for Iran’s gas export pipeline to Pakistan (IP) to become operational as soon as possible, Shana reported.
title: Pakistan willing IP to become operational very soon: Oji

description: Turkey, Iraq, Qatar and the United Arab Emirates on Tuesday signed a memorandum of understanding in Baghdad to cooperate on the Iraq Development Road project that would connect the Persian Gulf to Europe, during a visit by Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Monday.
title: Turkey, Iraq, Qatar and UAE sign transportation deal that hopes to connect Persian Gulf to Europe

description:
Food security and producing healthy and high-quality food to meet the country's needs is one of the strategic goals of the government. With the growth of investment in this sector, efforts have been made to provide food security, particularly by increasing milk and meat production.

Dasht Azarnegin Company is active in this sector. Animal husbandry, fish farming, and beekeeping are among the activities of the company.
title: Agro-food industries meet food security

description: TEHRAN – Iranian border police commander Brigadier General Ahmad-Ali Goudarzi in a meeting with Director General of Kuwait’s Coast Guard, Sheikh Mobarak Ali Al-Sabah, conferred on ways to enhance the security of maritime borders.
title: Iran, Kuwait discuss ways to beef up maritime border security

description: TEHRAN – Iran anti-narcotics police have seized some 580 tons of narcotics in the past Iranian calendar year 1402 (March 2023 –March 2024).
title: Police seize 580 tons of narcotics in a year

description: TEHRAN –According to Metrological Organization, since the beginning of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20),  the country has experienced an increase of 16 percent in precipitation compared to the same period a year before.
title: Rainfall increases by 16% since mid-March yr/yr

description: TEHRAN –Crisis prevention, as a crucial part of the crisis management process,  involves adopting a proactive approach to avoid or minimize the devastating effects of disasters and ensure a safe living environment, Mohammad-Hassan Nami, the head of the Crisis Management Organization, has said.
title: Proactive measures ensure a safe living environment: official

description: TEHRAN – With the conclusion of the 2024 Asian Wrestling Championships and the 2024 World Rowing Asian and Oceanian Olympic and Paralympic Qualification Regatta, Iran's contingent for the 2024 Paris Olympics has grown to 32 athletes.
title: Iran secures 32 Paris 2024 berths
